cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about convolutional neural networks applied to computer vision tasks, specifically semantic segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques and fine-tuning, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of fully convolutional networks, which are a type of neural network architecture (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the model on various datasets, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
